ers offer deep insights into a specific education system and, together, the studies allow for a comparison and holistic understanding of multilingualism in European education.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2023) 0aEducation, BilingualzEurope. 0aLanguage and languagesxStudy and teaching. 0aMultilingual educationzEurope. 0aMultilingualismzEurope. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh  aEuropean education systems.  abilingual education.  abilingualism.  aeducation.  alanguage education.  alanguage policy.  amultilingualism.1 aBastida, Carolina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBerg, Sjoerd van den, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCaballé, Ester, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDíaz-Torrent, Josep M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFernández-Costales, Alberto, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGamir, Saâdia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGonzález-Riaño, Xosé Antón, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHendriks, Berna, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHooft, Andreu van, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHuguet, Ángel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHuguet, Ángel, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aIanos, Adelina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJanés, Judit, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJiménez-Salcedo, Juan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLapresta-Rey, Cecilio, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.l